If one side of the expression is longer, putting the shorter one first can improve readability. (Some would argue that you should assign the longer expression to a variable first).<p>I think that<p><pre><code>  if(S_OK == QueryInterface(IID_IUnknown, &p)) {
</code></pre>
is clearer than<p><pre><code>  if(QueryInterface(IID_IUnknown, &p) == S_OK) {</code></pre>
